@startuml TestingLayer4Sequence
' SPEC source: internal/tmux/e2e_test.go
' Layer 4 — the promptful flow over time: drive -> prompt -> model -> side effect.
' Build tag: //go:build e2e; gate: PROVEO_LLM_TEST=1
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam shadowing false

title Layer 4 · Agent E2E — promptful flow (-tags=e2e; assert the side effect)

actor "E2E test / CI" as Test
participant "tmux (internal/tmux)" as Tmux
participant "harness TUI (docker run -it)" as Harness
participant "Ollama sidecar" as Ollama
database "output mount" as FS

Test -> Tmux : Start(proveo run <target> --local-model gemma4)
Tmux -> Harness : launch in headless PTY
note over Ollama : sidecar starts;\nmodel cold-loads on first call
Harness --> Tmux : prints ready prompt
Test -> Tmux : WaitFor("ready")
Tmux --> Test : matched

Test -> Tmux : SendText(task prompt) + Enter
Tmux -> Harness : keystrokes -> stdin
Harness -> Ollama : POST /v1/chat/completions (NO_PROXY)
note right of Ollama : cold-load can take minutes\n(wait-for-serving + long timeout)
Ollama --> Harness : reply (may include reasoning preamble)
Harness -> FS : write DONE.txt (marker)

loop poll until marker or timeout
  Test -> FS : read DONE.txt
end
Test -> Test : assert contains marker
Test -> Tmux : Kill (+ egress teardown)

note over Test, FS
Assert the **side effect** (DONE.txt), never the transcript — the model's prose
is non-deterministic. Poll with timeout; never a fixed sleep.
end note
@enduml
